==English==
===Etymology===
Derives from Latin ''hiatus, -us, m.'': gap; cf. hiare, hio, hiavi (hisco); (&#967;&#945;&#943;&#957;&#969;) &#941;-&#967;&#945;&#957;-&#959;&#957;, &#954;&#941;&#967;&#951;&#957;&#945;; Old High German gin&#275;n; German 'gähnen' -> "yawn")

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-hiatus.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''hiatus'''|'''[[hiatus]] '''or''' [[hiatuses]]'''}}

#A [[break]] or [[pause]].
#A [[gap]] in a [[series]], making it [[incomplete]].
#{{linguistics}}
##A [[syllable break]] between two [[vowel]]s, without an intervening [[consonant]]. (Compare [[diphthong]].)
##The condition of having such a break.
##:''Words like'' reality ''and'' naive ''contain vowels in hiatus.''
#A [[gap]] in [[geological]] [[strata]].
#A [[fissure]] in a [[bone]].
#A small [[difference]] in [[pitch]] between two [[musical]] [[tones]].

====Synonyms====
*[[break]] (1)

